{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, retrieval-augmented fine-tuning (RAFT) combines the advantages of RAG and fine-tuning, creating synthetic datasets for fine-tuning models to specific domains (Zhang et al. 2024).",
    "RAFT outperforms traditional RAG in specialized domains such as medicine.",
    "It involves the creation of a synthetic dataset of queries, relevant documents, and target responses.",
    "A model can be fine-tuned on this dataset to align it with the domain knowledge and style.",
    "RAFT allows the model to ''study'' the domain knowledge in advance, resulting in better performance than traditional RAG."
  ]
}